FT  27 JUN 92 / International Company News: Hellenic Bottling lifts earnings
45%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KERIN HOPE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ATHENS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
HELLENIC Bottling Company, the Cypriot-controlled soft drinks group which
holds the Coca-Cola franchises for Greece, Northern Ireland and Bulgaria,
lifted 1991 pre-tax profits by 45 per cent to Dr10.3bn (Dollars 54.2m),
writes Kerin Hope from Athens.
